The paper discusses the combination of human and machine classifiers to efficiently screen items that satisfy a set of predicates. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) to optimize the cost-accuracy trade-off. The paper also discusses the use of existing machine classifiers and the need to train an ensemble of classifiers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of test data to assess the accuracy of classifiers, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
